    "why": "This is because NICE guidelines recommend that oseltamivir (or zanamivir) can be used for the treatment of influenza in people who are otherwise healthy, but only if they present within 48 hours of the onset of symptoms\u00b9. Oseltamivir may shorten the duration of symptoms by about a day and may reduce the risk of complications such as otitis media, sinusitis, and lower respiratory tract infections\u00b2. However, oseltamivir is not a substitute for the influenza vaccine, which is the best way to prevent influenza and its complications",
